## ⚠️ Finding 4 — Missing Request Body Parsing & Input Validation (OWASP A03:2021) — **MEDIUM**

There is **no body-parsing middleware** registered. If this app is extended with `POST`/`PUT`/`PATCH` routes (the natural next step), request bodies will silently be `undefined`. Developers often bolt on parsing later without adding validation, creating injection and mass-assignment risks.

**✅ Recommended fix — add body parsers with size limits now, before routes are added:**

```js
// Limit body size to prevent payload-based DoS
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true, limit: '10kb' }));
```

**And validate/sanitize all user-supplied input**, e.g. with `express-validator`:

```js
const { body, validationResult } = require('express-validator');

app.post('/users',
  requireAuth,
  body('email').isEmail().normalizeEmail(),
  body('name').isString().trim().isLength({ min: 1, max: 100 }).escape(),
  (req, res) => {
    const errors = validationResult(req);
    if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
      return res.status(400).json({ errors: errors.array() });
    }
    // Safe to proceed
  }
);
```

