## 🚨 Finding 1 — Broken Access Control (OWASP A01:2021) — **HIGH**

**`/users` exposes PII with zero authentication or authorization.**

```js
// CURRENT — anyone on the internet can call this
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    { id: 2, name: 'Bob', email: 'bob@example.com' },
  ]);
});
```

Email addresses are Personally Identifiable Information (PII). There is no check for who is calling this endpoint — no token, no session, no role.

**✅ Recommended fix:**

```js
// Add authentication middleware (example using JWT)
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

function requireAuth(req, res, next) {
  const authHeader = req.headers['authorization'];
  const token = authHeader && authHeader.split(' ')[1]; // Bearer <token>

  if (!token) return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });

  jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET, (err, user) => {
    if (err) return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });
    req.user = user;
    next();
  });
}

// Apply to protected routes
app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
  // Only authorized users reach here
  res.json([ /* ... */ ]);
});
```

