## ⚠️ Finding 5 — No Error Handling Middleware (OWASP A05:2021) — **MEDIUM**

Without a global error handler, Express falls back to its **default error handler, which can leak full stack traces** (including file paths, line numbers, and dependency versions) to clients in development mode — and sometimes in production too.

**✅ Recommended fix — register a catch-all error handler as the last middleware:**

```js
// Must be defined AFTER all routes — 4 parameters signals error middleware to Express
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log the full error internally (never send it to the client)
  console.error({
    message: err.message,
    stack: err.stack,
    url: req.url,
    method: req.method,
  });

  const statusCode = err.status || err.statusCode || 500;

  // Send a safe, generic response to the client
  res.status(statusCode).json({
    error: statusCode === 500 ? 'Internal server error' : err.message,
  });
});
```

