**Problem:** Real names and email addresses are hardcoded directly in source code. Even if these are currently placeholders, this pattern invites real credentials or PII to end up committed to version control — a permanent, auditable leak.

**Fix:** Remove all hardcoded PII. Source user data exclusively from a database or an environment-controlled data store:

```js
