### 3. 🔴 Security Misconfiguration — Missing Security Headers (OWASP A05)

**Issue:** No HTTP security headers are set. This exposes users to clickjacking, MIME-sniffing attacks, XSS via reflected content, and more.

**Fix:** Add [`helmet`](https://helmetjs.github.io/), which sets a comprehensive set of protective headers in one line:

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
```

